	<p>22. SOUNDBITE (English) Heather Sebire, Senior property curator for Stonehenge at English Heritage:</p>
	<p>"They've gathered in lots of artifacts that relate to the time of Stonehenge. And I think they're demonstrating pre-history in general, but they're using Stonehenge as a sort of gateway because it's so iconic and a lot of the things do relate to Stonehenge. But I think it's going to give us a fantastic insight to the fact that those people, in a way, were just like us, but they just had different technologies and everything. It (the exhibition) will be absolutely fantastic. And we hope that by going to exhibition, people will want to come and see the real thing and we look forward to welcoming them when they do come."</p>
